Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper deals with wireless communication networks and their interference issues, which falls under the scope of this sub-category. 
2. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper discusses the use of directional antennas and their impact on interference, which is related to information theory. 
3. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper may be relevant to multimedia applications that require high-quality wireless communication, which can be achieved through the use of FD and directional antennas. 
4. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper may be relevant to the design and control of large-scale wireless networks, which require efficient interference management techniques. 
5. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) - The paper may be relevant to the security of wireless networks, as interference can be exploited by attackers to disrupt communication.
